               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400615-name-1250" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1250" type="surname" value="WALKLING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-1250" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS WALKLING.</persName>
                  </hi>I was at work in the fields at Eltham, on the 21st of May—I took off my coat and hung it in the hedge—I was hoeing back<lb></lb>wards and forwards till about ten o'clock, I then missed my coat, and I saw a hole made in the hedge as if some person had got through—I went round into the field, and by the hole there was a stick about six feet long with two prongs—I went and told the policeman—this is my coat which is now produced—the handkerchief, and bread and cheese were in the pocket.</p>
